Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer parameter `n` must be greater than or equal to 1.
- The integer parameter `k` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to `n`.
- The integer array parameter `relations` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `relations` must have a length less than or equal to `n * (n-1) / 2`.
- Each element in the integer array parameter `relations` must be an array of length 2.
- The elements in each array of the integer array parameter `relations` must be unique and within the range of `1` to `n`.
- The integer result is the minimum number of semesters needed to take all courses.